## 7. Concrete case: agri-food filling line

Imagine a filling line in a Tunisian agri-food factory.

The problem: frequent downtime on a capping machine.  
Management wants to “do predictive maintenance.”

Before choosing a model, you must map the data.

### Possible useful data

- motor vibration;
- motor temperature;
- electric current;
- line speed;
- number of stops;
- downtime duration;
- cause of downtime;
- product batch;
- bottle format;
- shift;
- maintenance intervention;
- replaced parts;
- scrap rate;
- cleaning or changeover.

### What you must check

- Is downtime historized?
- Are downtime causes reliable?
- Are sensor readings timestamped?
- Are maintenance interventions linked to the machine?
- Are format changes recorded?
- Will the model be able to alert before failure, not after it?

### Reasonable first decision

Do not start with a complex model.

Start with a condition-monitoring pilot:

- track vibration and temperature trends;
- link peaks to downtime;
- improve failure-cause entry;
- define a first alert threshold;
- test value on one critical machine.

This is often the right path toward predictive maintenance.

---

---

## 8. Edge, cloud, or local server?

Industrial data can be processed in several places.

### Edge

Edge processing happens near the machine or the line.

Useful when:

- reaction time is short;
- network connection is limited;
- data should not leave the site;
- production continuity is critical.

### Local server

A local server can centralize shop-floor data, historize signals, and host internal models.

Useful when the factory wants more control over data.

### Cloud

Cloud can facilitate storage, advanced analytics, and multi-site collaboration.

Useful when:

- several sites need to compare data;
- volumes are large;
- remote teams need access to analyses.

But cloud requires strict thinking about confidentiality, cybersecurity, cost, latency, and supplier dependency.

ISO/IEC 30141:2024 provides an IoT reference architecture with common vocabulary, reusable designs, and best practices. This type of reference helps structure technical choices without improvisation.

